<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="509" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,311,912]" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,511,383,408]" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">Comments and Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giordani Soika" authorityYear="1990" box="[894,1029,384,408]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humerale">
<emphasis box="[894,1029,384,408]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">S. humerale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both are relatively large compared to other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giordani Soika" authorityYear="1978" box="[384,512,420,443]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[384,512,420,443]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">Stenosigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, they present the integument with sparser punctation, rarely with concentrated and abundant punctures. In the pronotum and mesepisternum the punctures are sparse and deep.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,311,912]" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">
Two specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[409,531,492,516]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quechua">
<emphasis box="[409,531,492,516]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">S. quechua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were mistakenly included in the 
<typeStatus box="[903,951,493,517]" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giordani Soika" authorityYear="1990" box="[1060,1194,492,516]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humerale">
<emphasis box="[1060,1194,492,516]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">S. humerale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Giordani Soika as 
<typeStatus box="[151,262,528,552]" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">paratypes</typeStatus>
. The mistake was detected by 
<bibRefCitation box="[599,912,527,552]" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" refId="ref7987" refString="Hermes, M. G. &amp; Ferreira, W. D. (2016) On the type series Of Stenosigma humerale GiOrdani SOika With the descriptiOn Of a neW species (HymenOptera, Vespidae, EUmeninae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 60, 123 ¯ 127. https: // dOi. Org / 10.1016 / j. rbe. 2016.01.003" type="journal article">Hermes and Ferreira (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, and the main differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giordani Soika" authorityYear="1990" box="[1303,1436,528,552]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humerale">
<emphasis box="[1303,1436,528,552]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">S. humerale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[201,327,564,588]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quechua">
<emphasis box="[201,327,564,588]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">S. quechua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were detailed by these authors (
<bibRefCitation box="[704,1089,564,589]" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" refId="ref7987" refString="Hermes, M. G. &amp; Ferreira, W. D. (2016) On the type series Of Stenosigma humerale GiOrdani SOika With the descriptiOn Of a neW species (HymenOptera, Vespidae, EUmeninae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 60, 123 ¯ 127. https: // dOi. Org / 10.1016 / j. rbe. 2016.01.003" type="journal article">Hermes &amp; Ferreira, 2016, p. 125</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giordani Soika" authorityYear="1990" box="[1111,1355,564,588]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humerale">
<emphasis box="[1111,1355,564,588]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">Stenosigma humerale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Stenosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quechua">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">S. quechua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily distinguished by having the pre-apical fossa flattened and poorly developed in the former (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 31–35. 31, 32" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,327,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[152,1435,327,1940]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. 31, 32. T1, dOrsal; arrOW pOint tO pre-apical fOssa: FIGURES31. Stenosigma humerale (GiOrdani SOika); 32. S. quechua Hermes &amp; Ferreira. 33–35. S. panamensis Ferreira &amp; Hermes neW species, male genitalia: 33. AedeagUs in lateral VieW; 34. AedeagUs in Ventral VieW; 35. GOnOcOXite and VOlsella. Scale bar fOr Figs. 31, 32 = 1 mm; Figs. 33–35 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457493/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
), and slit-shaped in the latter (
<figureCitation box="[521,605,636,661]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35. 31, 32" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,327,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[152,1435,327,1940]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. 31, 32. T1, dOrsal; arrOW pOint tO pre-apical fOssa: FIGURES31. Stenosigma humerale (GiOrdani SOika); 32. S. quechua Hermes &amp; Ferreira. 33–35. S. panamensis Ferreira &amp; Hermes neW species, male genitalia: 33. AedeagUs in lateral VieW; 34. AedeagUs in Ventral VieW; 35. GOnOcOXite and VOlsella. Scale bar fOr Figs. 31, 32 = 1 mm; Figs. 33–35 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457493/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="509">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
